cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.PL 

This paper discusses the challenges of allocating resources to virtualized network functions and services to meet service level agreements, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of profiling techniques to support resource allocation decisions, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of profiling mechanisms into the NFV DevOps workflow, which is a topic related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
